race.comment: Tough race. MATROOSHI (7) was beaten at $1.55 last time at Warrnambool but may not have seen out the 1700m there having been very good in defeat over this trip prior. Comes back to her pet trip now and should take a power of catching. PHAROAH'S DAUGHTER (12) is another off a disappointing effort relative to her SP last time, finishing fifth at $2.35 but can be excused given the heavy ground at Geelong that day. Her form prior was good and she's worth another chance. SHE'S IMPECCABLE (3) got the job done in easier company at Warrnambool last start and could measure up with natural improvement. ANGELOS (8) is a lightly raced type who tackled a much stronger race last time, well beaten in the G2 Fillies Classic at Moonee Valley. She can bounce back. PINKERTON (10) is another off a maiden win who can figure.
